Why isn't this:
printNCSIControllerStats(const NCSIControllerPacketStats* stats)
std::cout << "TX stats" << stats->totalBytesTX;

I recommend changing this to use copy elision.
NCSIControllerPacketStatsResponse convertStatsToHostEndianess(NCSIControllerPacketStatsResponse *inVar)
{
    NCSIControllerPacketStatsResponse localVar{};
    // Do all the endianess conversions filling in the localVar
    localVar.countersClearedFromLastReadMSB = notohl(inVar.....);
    return localVar;  // will not copy, will use move semantics.
}

Change the passed parameter to a `const NCSIControllerPacket....& resp)`
if you use the prior change you can 
auto endianCorrect = convertStatsToHostEndianess(reinterpret_cast<NCSIControllerPacketStatsResponse*>nsl_data(tb[NCSI_ATTR_DATA])));
printNCSIControllerStats(endianCorrect);

Or just chain the two calls together eliminating the 'auto endianCorrect' var.
